article.headline: UC Irvine 78, Long Beach State 58
article.story: IRVINE, Calif. (AP) -- Jeff Gloger scored 20 points to tie his career high as he led UC Irvine to a 78-58 victory over Long Beach State Thursday night. Gloger made nine of 11 shots. Aaron Fitzgerald added 13 points and a career-best 11 assists, and Adam Metelski scored a career-high 12 points for the Anteaters (8-6, 3-4 Big West Conference). Jibril Hodges scored 16 points for the 49ers (2-14, 0-7), who have lost 17 consecutive conference games and 15 successive road games since Jan. 29, 2004. Gloger scored six points and Fitzgerald added five during a 15-0 surge that gave Irvine a 17-2 lead in the first 6:38. Long Beach missed nine successive shots and failed to score in a span of 6:24. The 49ers narrowed their deficit to 27-21 with 5:46 left in the first half, but Irvine's Greg Ethington scored five points during a 9-0 run that extended the Anteaters' lead to 36-21 with 2:04 before halftime. Irvine led by as many as 22 in the second half.
